    "html": "<div class=\"documentation-content routingdocumentation\">\n\n<div class=\"doc-title-bar\">\n  <h1 id=\"slice-routing\">\n    <span class=\"doc-title-text\">Slice Routing</span>\n    <span class=\"copy-md-slot\" data-copy-md></span>\n  </h1>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"overview\">Overview</h2>\n<p>Slice Router handles client-side navigation, route parameters, nested routes, and route containers. It auto-starts shortly after initialization, but you should call <code>start()</code> manually when you use guards to ensure your guard logic runs before the first navigation.</p>\n<p>Routing is driven by a <code>routes.js</code> file and a runtime router available at <code>slice.router</code>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"router-api\">Router API</h2>\n<div class=\"table-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-1\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"route-configuration\">Route Configuration</h2>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-2\"></div>\n<h3 id=\"route-definition-fields\">Route Definition Fields</h3>\n<div class=\"table-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-3\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"route-info-object\">Route Info Object</h2>\n<p>Guards and route events receive <code>to</code> and <code>from</code> objects created by the router.</p>\n<div class=\"table-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-4\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"basic-navigation\">Basic Navigation</h2>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-5\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"route-containers\">Route Containers</h2>\n<p>Slice provides two route container components:</p>\n<ul><li><code>slice-route</code> for a single path</li><li><code>slice-multi-route</code> for a list of routes</li></ul>\n<p>They cache components and call <code>update()</code> when a cached component is reused.</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-6\"></div>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-7\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"guards\">Guards</h2>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-8\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"route-change-events\">Route Change Events</h2>\n<p>The router emits <code>router:change</code> using EventManager when enabled. Otherwise it dispatches a <code>CustomEvent</code> on <code>window</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-block\" data-block-id=\"doc-block-9\"></div>\n<h2 id=\"best-practices\">Best Practices</h2>\n<div class=\"callout callout-tip\">Call <code>start()</code> after registering guards to avoid missing the first navigation.</div>\n<div class=\"callout callout-tip\">Use metadata flags to keep guard logic declarative and centralized.</div>\n<h2 id=\"gotchas\">Gotchas</h2>\n<div class=\"callout callout-warning\"><code>navigate()</code> is async. Await it when you depend on the next route being ready.</div>\n<div class=\"callout callout-warning\">Dynamic params use <code>${param}</code> syntax, not <code>:param</code>.</div>\n</div>\n",
